LAKE MARY, Fla. (AP) _ Faro Technologies Inc. (FARO) on Wednesday reported a loss of $9.7 million in its first quarter.The Lake Mary, Florida-based company said it had a loss of 53 cents per share. Losses, adjusted for stock option expense and non-recurring costs, came to 14 cents per share.The computer-aided measurement and imaging devices and software company posted revenue of $76.7 million in the period.For the current quarter ending in July, Faro Technologies expects its results to range from a loss of 17 cents per share to earnings of 4 cents per share.The company said it expects revenue in the range of $77 million to $85 million for the fiscal second quarter._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on FARO at https://www.zacks.com/ap/FARO